{
  "texts": [
    "This allows individual students to discuss and connect ideas and relate those ideas to larger course questions.",
    "The Integration Agent (example prompt below) can serve as a mentor, that is \"aware\" of what students are studying and of what instructors want students to understand about core concepts and can help students make connections between concepts.",
    "The Integration Agent exercise can be assigned narrowly (to make connections across two specific concepts during a part of a course) or more broadly as a persistent mentor who helps students make connections across a course.",
    "5 Instructors can request that students share a link to these conversations so that they can observe how student understanding evolves.",
    "This exercise can be assigned as a standalone task or revisited at intervals throughout the course, covering a variety of topics."
  ]
}